article.description: Kyle Wiltjer, Domantas Sabonis and Silas Melson each scored 15 points to help Gonzaga dominate both halves and beat San Francisco 86-48 on Saturday night.
article.headline: Gonzaga dominates San Francisco 86-48
article.story: SPOKANE, Wash. -- Kyle Wiltjer, Domantas Sabonis and Silas Melson each scored 15 points to help Gonzaga dominate both halves and beat San Francisco 86-48 on Saturday night. Josh Perkins added 13 points, six rebounds and five assists for the Bulldogs (17-5, 9-2 West Coast Conference), who stretched a 17-point halftime advantage to their largest lead at 84-43. Bryan Alberts scored 10 points and Kyle Dranginis grabbed 10 rebounds. Gonzaga shot 15 of 37 from 3-point range with Melson sinking five and Wiltjer and Perkins adding three each. Uche Ofoegbu led the Dons (11-10, 5-6) with 16 points and Devin Watson scored 11. The Bulldogs opened with an 8-0 run and had a 14-point lead before the midpoint of the first half. San Francisco cut it down to six before Gonzaga closed the first half with an 11-0 run to lead 39-22. When Gonzaga beat the Dons 102-94 in overtime on Jan. 3 in San Francisco, it needed a late rally to overcome a 16-point, second-half deficit.
